@node "usage" "Discription"
@{b}@{u}Discription@{ub}@{uu}

If you want to use MouseCase, you must first copy the program to c: and
then you must take the entry 'MouseCase' in your Startup-Sequence at a
place where you want to start the program or script.
Then after a RESET hold down a special mousebutton combination and the
program or script will be executed.

Then copy the preference program in a drawer of your choice, best the
'Prefs'-drawer.
The usage of the preferece program is very easy:

               .----------------------------.
               |@{"Load" link load}   @{"Save" link save}   @{"About" link about}   @{"Quit" link quit}|
               |----------------------------|
               |@{" " link mouse}@{"       MouseButtons       " link mouse}|
               |----------------------------|
               |@{"Open..." link open}@{"                    " link string}|
               |@{"StartĀOptions " link startoptions}@{" StopĀOptions" link breakoptions}|
               |----------------------------|
               |Status|____________________||
               `----------------------------'
@endnode

@node "load" "Load"
@{b}@{u}Load@{ub}@{uu}

Loads the saved preferences 'mousecase.prefs' from s: drawer into the
program.
@endnode

@node "save" "Save"
@{b}@{u}Save@{ub}@{uu}

Saves the actual settings to 's:mousecase.prefs'.
@endnode

@node "about" "About"
@{b}@{u}About@{ub}@{uu}

Shows informations about this program.
@endnode

@node "quit" "Quit"
@{b}@{u}Quit@{ub}@{uu}

Quits the program. All datas which were not saved at this time will be lost.
@endnode

@node "mouse" "MouseButtons"
@{b}@{u}MouseButtons@{ub}@{uu}

Here you can select the button combinations.
With a 3-button-mouse seven combinations are possible.

@{bg fill}Left              @{bg background}
@{bg fill}Right             @{bg background}
@{bg fill}Left+Right        @{bg background}
@{bg fill}Center            @{bg background}
@{bg fill}Left+Center       @{bg background}
@{bg fill}Center+Right      @{bg background}
@{bg fill}Left+Center+Right @{bg background}
@endnode

@node "open" "Filerequester"
@{b}@{u}Open...@{ub}@{uu}

Opens a filerequester to select a program or a script-file easily.
@endnode

@node "string" "Stringgadget"
@{b}@{u}Stringgadget@{ub}@{uu}

Here you can enter filenames and pathes by hand.
Keep care about the correction of your input !
Because if you do a wrong input the execution will be failed.
@endnode

@node "startoptions" "Startoptions"
@{u}@{b}Start Settings@{ub}@{uu}

Here you can make some special adjustments about the start of programs
respectivly the execution of scripts.

@{bg fill}Run    @{bg background}     - program will be started with RUN
@{bg fill}Runback@{bg background}     - program will be started with 'RUN >NIL:'
@{bg fill}Batch  @{bg background}     - a script will be executed
@endnode

@node "breakoptions" "Stopoptions"
@{u}@{b}Break Settings@{ub}@{uu}

Some times it could be nessessary to stop the execution of the startscript
after starting a program or executing a script.
In this case the followings settings should help you.

@{bg fill}None       @{bg background}     - the script execution doesn't stop
@{bg fill}Shell Break@{bg background}     - the selected options will be executed and after
                  that the execution will be stopped
@{bg fill}Break Only @{bg background}     - only the execution of the script will be stopped
                  (all settings will be ignored)
@endnode

